            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_268gc' title='Col. 268GC &mdash; HL Deb 02 February 2004 vol 656 c268GC' name='column_268gc' href='#column_268gc' rel='bookmark'>268GC</a>
            purposes of a trial? That would at least place some limit on what is meant by a sample case. That is the usual situation with a sample count. Often, a sample count is taken but all the evidence relating to a course of conduct is introduced to prove that particular count. If we can confine a sample count to a situation where all the other counts are admissible on the similar fact principle, I should be grateful. Can the Minister give that assurance?
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
